{{Infobox handball club | clubname = '''Nordsjælland Håndbold''' | image = | fullname = | short name = | founded = 2006 | ground = [[Helsingør-hallen]] | capacity = 2,500 | chairman = Jørgen Simonsen | manager = Ian Marko Fog | league = [[Danish Handball League|888ligaen]] | season = [[2017–18 Håndboldligaen|2017–18]] | position = 7th | website = http://www.nordsjaelland-haandbold.dk/ | colour1 = green | colour2 = black | pattern_la1 = | pattern_b1 = | pattern_ra1 = | pattern_sh1 = | leftarm1 = | body1 = | rightarm1 = | shorts1 = | pattern_la2 = | pattern_b2 = | pattern_ra2 = | pattern_sh2 = | leftarm2 = | body2 = | rightarm2 = | shorts2 = }}
'''Nordsjælland Håndbold''' is a [[team handball|handball]] club, based in [[Helsinge (town)|Helsinge]], [[Denmark]]. Currently, Nordsjælland Håndbold competes in the men's [[Danish Handball League]], and plays its home matches in [[Helsinge-Hallen]] in [[Helsinge (town)|Helsinge]]. The women's team is competing in the third-best tier of the women's Danish league system.
==History== The club was founded in 2006, when '''Team Helsinge''' and '''Hillerød HK''' merged their first teams to create the new club. The following season, the team gained promotion to the [[Danish Handball League]]. ==Team== ===Staff=== :''Staff for the 2018-19 season'' {| class="wikitable" style="text-align: left;" !valign=center |Pos.||Name |- |- |Head Coach||Ian Marko Fog |- |Assistant Coach||Simon Dahl |- |Assistant Coach||Per Nielsen |- |}
