{{Infobox NRHP | name = Two Buttes Gymnasium | nrhp_type = | image = Two Buttes Gymnasium.JPG | caption = The property in 2015. | location= 5th and C Sts., [[Two Buttes, Colorado]] | coordinates = {{coord|37|33|36|N|102|23|55|W|display=inline,title}} | locmapin = Colorado#USA | built = 1935-37 | builder = [[Works Progress Administration]] | architecture = [[Late 19th and Early 20th Century American Movements architecture|Late 19th and Early 20th Century American Movements]], [[WPA Rustic]] | added = December 22, 2009 | area = {{convert|1.7|acre}} | governing_body = Local | mpsub = New Deal Resources on Colorado's Eastern Plains MPS | refnum = 09001119<ref name="nris">{{NRISref|version=2010a}}</ref> }} The '''Two Buttes Gymnasium''' is an [[ashlar]] [[sandstone]]-walled {{convert|60|x|130|ft|m|adj=on}} single-story gym building located at 5th and C Sts. in [[Two Buttes, Colorado]]. It was built during 1935–37 as a [[Works Progress Administration]] (WPA) project in style that has been termed [[WPA Rustic|WPA Rustic architecture]].<ref name=nris/><ref name=copres/>
The building has served as a sports facility and as a meeting hall. It was listed on the [[National Register of Historic Places]] in 2009.<ref name=nris/>
Its construction employed 36 persons, and used stone from eight separate local quarries.<ref name=copres>{{cite web|url=http://coloradopreservation.org/programs/cultural-resource-surveys/new-deal-survey-2/new-deal-resources-on-the-national-register/two-buttes-gymnasium/ |title=Two Buttes Gymnasium |publisher=Colorado Preservation}}</ref> <ref name=sec>{{cite web|url=http://www.secoloradoheritage.com/heritage-attractions/two-buttes-gymnasium.1 |title=Two Buttes Gymnasium |publisher=Southeast Colorado |deadurl=bot: unknown |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120224015528/http://www.secoloradoheritage.com/heritage-attractions/two-buttes-gymnasium.1 |archivedate=2012-02-24 |df= }} (includes photo) ()</ref> <!--- NRHP nom doc seems not available on-line <ref name=nrhpdoc>{{cite web|url=http://pdfhost.focus.nps.gov/docs/NRHP/Text/09001119.pdf |title=National Register of Historic Places Inventory/Nomination: Two Buttes Gymnasium / 5BA.1146 |author= |date= |publisher=National Park Service}} and [http://pdfhost.focus.nps.gov/docs/NRHP/Photos/09001119.pdf accompanying photos]</ref> ---->
