{{infobox country at games | NPC = UGA | NPCname = Uganda National Paralympic Committee | games = Summer Paralympics | year = 1976 | flagcaption = | oldcode = | website = | location = [[Toronto]] | competitors = 1 | sports = 1 | flagbearer = | rank = 34 | gold = 0 | silver = 0 | bronze = 0 | officials = | appearances = auto | app_begin_year = | app_end_year = | summerappearances = | winterappearances = | seealso = }} '''[[Uganda]]''' sent a delegation to compete at the '''[[1976 Summer Paralympics]]''' in [[Toronto]], [[Ontario]], Canada. The country entered only one athlete, who competed in [[Athletics at the 1972 Summer Paralympics|athletics]]. He did not win a medal.<ref>[http://www.paralympic.org/Sport/Results/search.html?npc=UGA&gender=all&medal=all&sport=all&games=all Uganda at the Paralympics], [[International Paralympic Committee]]</ref>
Uganda competed in the Paralympics, but not in the [[1976 Summer Olympics]],<ref>[http://www.olympic.org/en/content/Olympic-Games/All-Past-Olympic-Games/Summer/Montreal-1976/ Montreal 1976], Olympic Movement</ref> as it took part in the [[1976 Summer Olympics#Boycotting countries|African boycott]] of that year's Summer Games.
It was to be Uganda's last appearance at the Summer Paralympics before 1996.
==Athletics== {{main|Athletics at the 1976 Summer Paralympics}}
[[O. Obadiya]] <small>(full name not recorded)</small> was Uganda's only representative, and competed in the [[Athletics at the 1976 Summer Paralympics - Men's javelin throw C|men's javelin throw (C category)]]. He finished 15th out of 23, with a throw of 32.18m.<ref>[http://www.paralympic.org/Sport/Results/search.html?npc=UGA&gender=all&medal=all&sport=all&games=all Uganda at the Paralympics], [[International Paralympic Committee]]</ref>
