{{Infobox Stadium | stadium_name= Şenol Güneş Spor Kompleksi Medical Park Arena | image = Şenol Güneş Stadyumu - Medical Park Arena.jpg | image_size = 300px | former_names = | location = [[Trabzon]], [[Turkey]] | coordinates = {{coord|40|59|56.8|N|39|38|45.4|E|type:landmark|display=inline,title}} | broke_ground = November 24, 2013 | opened = December 18, 2016 | surface =[[Hybrid grass]] | construction_cost = 230.000.000 TL | architect = ASP Stuttgart | seating_capacity= 43,223 | record_attendance = {{formatnum: 38477}} ([[Trabzonspor]]–[[Fenerbahçe S.K.|Fenerbahçe]], 28 January 2018) | suites = 122 | tenants = [[Trabzonspor]] |website=}}
'''Şenol Güneş Stadium''' ({{lang-tr|Şenol Güneş Stadyumu}}), known as '''Medical Park Arena''' for sponsorship reasons, is a [[stadium]] located in [[Trabzon]], [[Turkey]].<ref>[http://www.yenisafak.com/spor/akyazi-arenanin-acilis-tarihi-netlesti-2541602 Akyazı Arena'nın açılış tarihi netleşti]</ref><ref>[http://spor.haber7.com/futbol/haber/2152028-trabzonsporun-yeni-stadi-akyazi-arenanin-son-halinin-fotograflari Trabzonspor'un yeni stadı Akyazı Arena'nın son halinin fotoğrafları]</ref> It opened to public in December 2016 and has a capacity of 43,223 spectators.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.tff.org/Resources/Tamsaha/UEFA_EURO24_Bid_Brochure/50/|title=UEFA EURO24 Bid Brochure|work=[[Turkish Football Federation]]|page=50}}</ref> It is the new home of [[Trabzonspor]] of the [[Süper Lig]], replacing [[Hüseyin Avni Aker Stadium]]. It is named after the Turkish [[Manager (association football)|football manager]] and former [[Goalkeeper (association football)|goalkeeper]] of [[Trabzonspor]] and [[Turkey national football team]], [[Şenol Güneş]].
In 2017 stadium cooperates with [[FUNTORO]], installing interactive monitors in press seats, which provides live streaming, advertising system, players information etc.
